ght cause a second static initialization, but no, that's unlikely.\\n\\nI’m trying to understand why my earlier attempts may not have worked. The isolated ClassPool might not have received coverage since the Loader loaded the application from the class file, potentially delegating to the parent class. There’s a specific check for `javassist.Loader`, but not for `javassist.ClassPool`. \\n\\nIt's tricky because ClassPool$1 is package-private, meaning that when ClassPool initializes, it loads ClassPool$1 too. If the tests didn’t run due to compilation issues, that could explain the lack of coverage.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yucjRt7rWnTkhqlbH0hJ0Tbl|fc_001ae5f13463d4d10169f50efda7a0819ea5a875960d4da103", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath /home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/88b21d1ef06323beff58664cffa62848c033ecd2/javassist-3.12.0.GA.jar -c -p javassist.ClassPool | rg -n \"class\\$|Class\\.forName|getDeclaredMethod|anewarray\" -C 3"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 12156, "output": 1853, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38073, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777667809737, "responseId": "resp_001ae5f13463d4d10169f50ee2cee8819e9b8c835e952f345d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_yucjRt7rWnTkhqlbH0hJ0Tbl|fc_001ae5f13463d4d10169f50efda7a0819ea5a875960d4da103", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "240-        19: getfield      #12                 // Field cflow:Ljava/util/Hashtable;\n241-        22: aload_1\n242-        23: iconst_2\n243:        24: anewarray     #43                 // class java/lang/Object\n244-        27: dup\n245-        28: iconst_0\n246-        29: aload_2\n--\n592-         0: aload_1\n593-         1: ifnonnull     9\n594-         4: iconst_0\n595:         5: anew