pI-Oukp8sTGDn7QZ2An2YyK29iVGLwzKsCUx4hx-WNY58uHkSq7t8Nk3-CtsQ__Y3MtJiYVq-dz8VRYjtxo3RXOOs77vHf3cRcJNWyo_ygGdfrxHUZPv6Dj2zGgHSsu51bHLAc8yhJ6oV2U3nF7chs0JsnIHrjntNbSZFmC6LZxkTKoZaj_tJzhyooOgNobJCtF2FxMQkthp8bHfmTsL6QM-FjRGC1ShaksZBhaIo37-9HRIcrchKSzv9jpvLR_iNUZ4k8Ku0sLodUQbSPIDtdGM6Ouo5_snx9PEfWWU6XAnaCh3tvnK3G3wDPqoOMSYtcyGmz0K3ZMgtZaQIgyPYijTjlguak0UzvAigmw4Gi3sTWWmWhOPTpcYdTuoJsX4DVUmp8tmtm_0uo=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading options**\\n\\nI’m considering using Java’s `URLClassLoader` as a public class loading API for testing dynamic class loading. The user’s request includes loading classes and catching errors, but directly using reflection may lead to contamination. Instead, I think it’s better to implement a `Runnable` helper that can load a child class. However, reflections for testing purposes seem tricky. I might look into using `ClassLoader.loadClass` to avoid unnecessary initialization. It feels a bit complicated, but possible!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class loading alternatives**\\n\\nThe user mentioned not to use reflection directly, so I’m considering using `URLClassLoader.findClass` as an alternative. I could define the class to resolve it without initialization. I’m also thinking about the `ServiceLoader.load` method, which requires including a service file. To do this, the helper class must implement the service interface. I’ll check if Gradle tests allow including resources, and potentially add a service provider file under `src/test/resources/META-INF/services/`. It’s a bit broad, but worth exploring!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Javassist functionality**\\n\\nI’m considering if the Javassist source compiler allows for a `$` method. I need to check a specific source string I have: a method called `lookup` that returns a class using `javassist.ClassPool.class$`. In Java, the `$` character is allowed in class names. Since the method has package access and shares the same package as the generated class, it seems likely that Javassist should be able to resolve this method using ClassPool. I'll look into it further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ksHkkgtFl8EXIxcbGINsnKfd|fc_001ae5f13463d4d10169f50f38e0f8819eaf3bcfb70c6b02b2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/ClassPoolTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import javassist.ClassPool;\nimport javassist.CtClass;\nimport javassist.Loader;\n", "newText": "import javassist.ClassPool;\nimport javassist.CtClass;\nimport javassist.CtNewMethod;\n"}, {"oldText": "public class ClassPoolTest {\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \"javassist_javassist.ClassPoolGeneratedTarget\";\n    private static final String ISOLATED_RESULT_PROPERTY = \"javassist.classpool.isolated.result\";\n", "newText": "public class ClassPoolTest {\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_NAME = \"javassist_javassist.ClassPoolGeneratedTarget\";\n    private static final String LOOKUP_BRIDGE_CLASS_NAME = \"javassist.ClassPoolClassLookupBridge\";\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void loaderRunInitializesClassPoolInIsolatedNamespace() throws Throwable {\n        System.clearProperty(ISOLATED_RESULT_PROPERTY);\n        Loader loader = new Loader();\n\n        try {\n            loader.run(ClassPoolLoaderApplication.class.getName(), new String[0]);\n\n            assertThat(System.getProperty(ISOLATED_RESULT_PROPERTY)).isEqualTo(int.class.getName());\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            verifyUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\n        } finally {\n            System.clearProperty(ISOLATED_RESULT_PROPERTY);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void verifyUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(Error error) {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void generatedSamePackageBridgeUsesClassPoolClassLookup() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            ClassPool classPool = new ClassPool(true);\n            CtClass bridgeClass = classPool.makeClass(LOOKUP_BRIDGE_CLASS_NAME);\n            bridgeClass.setSuperclass(classPool.get(ClassNameLookup.class.getName()));\n            bridgeClass.addMethod(CtNewMethod.make(\n                    \"public Class lookup(String name) { return javassist.ClassPool.class$(name); }\",\n                    bridgeClass));\n\n            ClassNameLookup lookup = (ClassNameLookup) classPool.toClass(\n                    bridgeClass,\n                    ClassPoolTest.class.getClassLoader(),\n                    ClassPoolTest.class.getProtectionDomain()).newInstance();\n\n            assertThat(lookup.lookup(String.class.getName())).isSameAs(String.class);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            verifyUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void verifyUnsupportedDynamicClassLoading(Error error) {\n"}, {"oldText": "\n    public static class ClassPoolLoaderApplication {\n        public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n            ClassPool classPool = ClassPool.getDefault();\n            CtClass intClass = classPool.get(int.class.getName());\n\n            System.setProperty(ISOLATED_RESULT_PROPERTY, intClass.getName());\n        }\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "\n    public abstract static class ClassNameLookup {\n        public abstract Class<?> lookup(String name);\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 958, "output": 3662, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43020, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777667851559, "responseId": "resp_001ae5f13463d4d10169f50f0c2144819ea8e04bf0c7a29af1"}}
